{"key":"post-11977395","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11977395</id>\n<content>Lots of people use towels, although I feel it's a lot more work than steaming.&amp;nbsp; I wouldn't want to try it with grass seed though.&amp;nbsp; They're awfully small, and besides, it's best not to simmer or soak them other than in the jar itself.&amp;nbsp; Otherwise, you can end up with a big mess. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With grass seed, simply use twice as much seed by volume as water or water/coffee, add a pinch of gypsum and give the jar a shake.&amp;nbsp; Let sit for awhile and shake again.&amp;nbsp; Place lid with holes and filter, cover with foil and sterilize.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11977401</next>\n<prev>11977390</prev>\n<first>11975858</first>\n<last>11977481</last>\n<when>1265507419</when>\n<utime>02/07/10 03:50 AM</utime>\n</post>"}